dict.string: Nothing to see here yet... Check again later!
I love reading "[STORY_NAME]", check it out!

Although My Story is free to play, some in-game items may be purchased for real money. In case you want to disable this feature, turn off in-app purchases in your device's settings. Also, you must be at least 13 years of age in order to play.
[FRIEND_NAME] just finished reading [STORY_NAME]! What would you recommend them to read next?
[FRIEND_NAME] just started reading [STORY_NAME]! Have you read it?
[FRIEND_NAME] just reviewed [STORY_NAME]! Check out their profile to read it!
You got a role in a movie! Will your first taste of Hollywood fame also be your last one? Find out what happens next in Hollywood in Heels!
Chantelle’s party was a blast, but there’s something new in store for you... Find out what by reading next chapter of Hollywood in Heels!
You moved into your new apartment, and you got into a fight with Sophie... Did Nicki betray you? Will she ruin your new career? Find out in chapter 7!
Oh no! You fell while walking the red carpet and now everyone’s talking about it! Will this affect your and Zack’s relationship in next chapter?
You had a lovely date with Zack, but it was interrupted by a mystery phone call... Who was it? Find out in chapter 9!
Jessica was your mystery caller! But... Why? The answer is waiting for you in next chapter of Hollywood in Heels!
Jenna is pregnant?? With your BOYFRIEND out of all people? Oh no, what are you going to do? Go make some choices in chapter 11!
Amber is missing! Does Jenna have something to do with it? Will you confront her in chapter 12?
Jenna is on the run and Zack dumped you... Who needs them, anyway? A new chapter is waiting for you!
What is going on with Danny’s mother? Do you want to find out more? Go read chapter 5 of Who Wants To Marry Miss Larson!
Your character is going to relax today, and so should you! Chapter 6 is waiting for you!
Running into your ex boyfriend while on a date is never fun... Well, almost never, since chapter 7 is a great exception to this rule!
Brad has warned you about Ricardo, but who will you trust? Make a choice in chapter 8!
Oops! Ricardo found out you were trying to tape him! What will you do in chapter 9?
Cece is testing your suitors! Which one will fail? Find out in chapter 10!
Tommy fell for Cece, which means he’s going home. If only you could actually find him... Well, you can always read another chapter and find out what happens next!
You’re going on a vacation! Are you excited? Chapter 12 is waiting for you!
Jackson kissed you last night, but you still have a date with Jimmy... Could there be more to his somber demeanor?
Something is wrong with Brad... Can you guess what it is? Chapter 14 is ready!
Brad hasn’t been feeling well, and it looks like one of the guys has been lying to you... The plot thickens in chapter 15!
It’s time to eliminate someone once again! Who will it be? Chapter 16, here we come!
Danny has to talk to you about something, but Damien interrupted you with his bad news! How are you going to react?
It is getting hot and steamy out there, and guys are getting jealous... It doesn’t help that you have three dates in one day waiting for you!
Eliminating Jimmy was one of the hardest decisions you had to make, but you are certain you made the right choice. Or did you? Chapter 19 is ready!
The final chapter is waiting for you. Who will you choose, Jackson or Danny? Don’t keep them waiting!
Was saving a dance for Preston such a good idea? Hunter might have something to say about it in chapter 5 of The Bitten Ones...
What is going on between Preston and Trish? Are they truly broken up? Come back for chapter 6!
What has Aly taken? Save your friend in chapter 7 of The Bitten Ones!
What do you know about werewolves? The library might be a good place to start learning more...
Trish put you under a freezing spell! How will you get out of this situation? Chapter 9 is waiting for you!
Hunter is ignoring you, and Preston has disappeared again... Looks like your love life is in shambles. Go fix it in chapter 10!
Trish and Preston are back together?? What is happening?? Chapter 11 contains some answers!
You’ve finally discovered your power... Can you guess what it is?
Trish is your sister and Serena is your mother? What...? It’s time to get some answers about your past in chapter 13!
You found out that Elvira was interested in werewolves... Did that have something to do with her disappearance? Chapter 14 is waiting for you!
This is it. Time to get some answers from Dolph. Are you excited about the final chapter of The Bitten Ones?
Stacy brought a prom date, but he keeps disappearing... Can you guess who it is before reading chapter 5 of Dear Mona?
OMG! Mark is back in town! He better have some good excuse for leaving in chapter 6!
Did something happen between Mark and Stacy last night? Find out directly from the source in chapter 7!
Mark invited you to meet him, but you already have plans with Shawn... Who will you choose in chapter 8?
You spent the night in Mark’s arms, but there is a certain someone who will not be overjoyed... Chapter 9 is waiting for you!
Telling Shawn what happened would be a wise choice, but how will he react? Find out in chapter 10!
You’ve been feeling sick for awhile... And there’s some new boy drama waiting for you in chapter 11!
Are you pregnant? Or is something else happening to your body? Chapter 12 will solve the mystery for you!
You are pregnant and you don’t know who the father is... But Max might have some advice for you in chapter 13!
You have some big news... But how are you going to tell the boys? Chapter 14 is waiting for you!
Not only are boys shocked because of your pregnancy, but it also seems that Mark has moved on... What is he doing in chapter 15?
Are you keeping the baby? Be careful, though, because Stacy might have something bad in store for you in chapter 16!
How will everyone react to your news? Find out in chapter 17!
OMG! The whole school has gone crazy in chapter 18 of Dear Mona!
Why would Mark’s mom go berserk? You definitely want to know what happens in chapter 19!
Your father had a genetic disease... Oh no, is your baby okay? Chapter 20 is waiting for you!
Taking a few days off with Mark seems like a good idea... Will he finally spit out the truth in chapter 21?
OMG! You are finally going to find out why Mark left three years ago in chapter 22!
What will be your baby’s favorite food? Mrs. Lee will tell you in chapter 23!
You’ve been ignoring Mark lately, but he’s having none of it. Check out chapter 24!
Mrs. Lee is offering you a job in chapter 25! And who in the world is Rhonda?
The test results are in! Is your baby healthy? Find out in chapter 26!
Your baby shower is happening right now! Join us in chapter 27!
Will you help Blair get Rolph back in chapter 28 of Dear Mona? Now’s your chance!
Mrs. Lee is having yet another vision of your future, but this time it sounds ominous... Go read all about it in chapter 29!
You’re 8 months pregnant, but you still have no clue who the father is... Or maybe you do? Chapter 30 is waiting for you!
You have your doubts about the father of your baby, but what about the gender? There is a party happening in chapter 31!
Are you having a girl or a boy? Find out the answer in chapter 32!
Your water just broke! Prepare for the delivery in chapter 33!
Whoever said that giving birth is no big deal was a giant liar. Luckily all of your friends are there in chapter 34!
Here it is, the final decision you have to make. Mark or Shawn? Shawn or Mark? Pick the guy in chapter 35!
The murderer accidentally left a clue in the form of an address. Will you take the matter into your own hands? Chapter 5 of For You, My Love is waiting for you!
Someone tried to break into your house... You won't be too happy when you find out who it was in chapter 6!
Dana has been murdered... What if you're next? Can you stop this madness? Chapter 7 is waiting for you!
The murderer has texted you... Can the police find out who it is before it's too late? It's time to read chapter 8!
This has been a crazy week, but at least Jerry is taking you out for dinner. The question is, will your evening truly be relaxing?
You know who the murderer is... But it might already be too late to stop him. Can you survive the final chapter of For You, My Love?
Come back to My Story, your characters need you!
Come back to My Story, your characters are waiting for you!
Come back and choose your path. Your characters await!
Want to live another life? Play My Story and choose your own path!
Come back and tell your own story. Your characters are waiting!
Come back to My Story, your story needs to be told!
Hey, don't miss out on your daily challenge!
Use your ticket and start reading!
Your ticket is here! Start reading!

Nanobit Ltd. ("Nanobit" or "we") provides this privacy policy (the "Policy") to describe the ways we collect, store, use, and manage the information, including personal information, that you provide or we collect in connection with our websites, including www.nanobit.co (the "Sites") or any Nanobit game provided on a mobile platform (for example, iOS and Android) (collectively: the "Service"). Please note that the scope of this Policy is limited to information collected or received by Nanobit through your use of the Service. Personal information is only collected in so far as it is technically required to provide the Service. In no case will the data collected be sold or unlawfully passed on to third parties for any other reasons. Nanobit is not responsible for the actions of third party people or companies, the content of their sites, the use of information you provide to them, or any products or services they may offer. Any link to those sites does not constitute our sponsorship of, or affiliation with those people or companies.

By using the Service, you are expressing your agreement to this Policy and the processing of your data, including your personal information, in the manner provided in this Policy. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use the Service.

When you use any of the Nanobit Services on a mobile platform, we collect and record certain information such as your unique device ID (persistent / non-persistent), hardware type, media access control ("MAC") address, international mobile equipment identity ("IMEI"), the version of your operating system ("OS"), your device name, your email address (if you have connected to Facebook or Google+), and your location (based on your Internet Protocol ("IP") address). This information is useful to us for troubleshooting and helps us understand usage trends. We do not collect and process personally identifiable information such as your name, date of birth, address and other, unless you provide us with them. In addition, we create a unique user ID to track your use of our Service ("Nanobit ID"). Nanobit ID is stored in connection with your profile information to track the Nanobit games you are playing.

Due to proper functioning, particular games require additional data. If you choose not to accept those terms you may not be able to install or to play the game. Additional data required include Location – we may collect your location-based information for the purpose of providing you with the correct version of the application. We will not share this information with any third party. If you no longer wish to allow us to track or use this information, you may turn it off at the device level or uninstall the game. We also may collect In-app purchase info, Device and app History, Contacts, Storage, Wi-Fi connection information, Photo/media/files for the gameto work properly. Whenever you play our games, we collect data about your interactions with the game and with the other players inside the game via server log files. This information may be associated with your Nanobit ID, IP address or device ID for the purpose of providing you our Services and improving them. This data is stored within Amazon Web Services, located in USA and secured by Amazon Web Services privacy policy.

While you are browsing Nanobit's Sites, your device's operating system, Internet Protocol (IP) address, access times, browser type and language and referring website addresses may be logged automatically. We use this information to monitor, develop and analyze your use of the Service.
We may collect your email address when you contact our customer service to be able to respond to your requests.

We will occasionally send you push notifications through our mobile applications to send you game updates, high scores and other notifications related to the Service that may be of importance to you. You may at any time opt-out from receiving these types of communications by turning them off at the device level through your settings.

Nanobit may offer you the opportunity to invite your contacts from a Social Network Service (such as your Facebook friends) so that those contacts can be located in Nanobit games and/or you can invite them to join you in Nanobit games. Such contact information will be used only for the purpose of sending communications to the addressee.

We use technologies such as cookies, beacons, scripts, and tags to identify a user's device and to "remember" things about your visit, such as your preferences or a user name and password. Information contained in a cookie may be linked to your personal information, such as your Nanobit ID, for purposes such as improving the quality of our Services, tailoring recommendations to your interests, and making the Service easier to use. You can disable cookies at any time, although you may not be able to access or use features of the Service. We may feature advertisements served by third-parties that deliver cookies to your computer/device so the content you access and advertisements you see can be tracked. Since the third-party advertising companies associate your computer/device with a number, they will be able to recognize your computer/device each time they send you an advertisement. These advertisers use information about your visits to our Service and third-party sites and applications in order to measure advertisement performance and to provide advertisements about goods and services of interest to you. This Policy does not apply to, and we are not responsible for the data collection practices of these third-party advertisers, and we encourage you to check their privacy policies to learn more about their use of cookies and other technology.

We may feature advertising within our Service. The advertisers collect and use information about you, such as your Service session activity, device identifier, MAC address, IMEI, geo-location information and IP address. They use this information to provide advertisements of interest to you. In addition, you may see our games advertised in other services. After clicking on one of these advertisements and installing our game, you will become a user of our Service. In order to verify the installs, a device identifier may be shared with the advertiser.

We use analytics software to allow us to better understand the functionality of our Services on your device. This software may record information such as how often you use the application, the events that occur within the application, aggregated usage, performance data, and where the application was downloaded from. We do not link the information we store within the analytics software to any personal information you submit within the mobile application.

Our website and games may contain advertising or third-party services (such as the Facebook Like button or links to third party websites). If you click on those links, including an advertisement, you will leave our Service and go to the site you selected. If you visit a third-party website or use a third-party service, you should consult that site's or service's privacy policy. Our privacy policy does not cover the use of tracking tools from third parties. We do not have access or control over these third parties.

Our Sites offer publicly accessible community forums and private messages. In order to use your community forum, you must register and provide a username, password and email address. You should be aware that any information you provide in these areas may be read, collected, and used by others who access them. To request removal of your personal information from our community forum, contact us at dpo@nanobit.co. In some cases, we may not be able to remove your personal information, in which case we will let you know if we are unable to do so and why.If you choose to use Facebook login to use our community forums, the information you provide is tied to your Facebook account. You will need to contact Facebook directly in order to request removal of personal information from our community forum.

We may also acquire information from you through your access and participation in message boards on the Service, your participation in surveys, sweepstakes or contests through the Service. Participation in these sweepstakes and contests is voluntary. The requested information typically includes contact information (such as name and shipping address), and demographic information (such as zip code).

Nanobit employs reasonable administrative, physical and electronic measures designed to help protect your information from unauthorized access. No security, however, can eliminate the possibility that your information may be accessed by an unauthorized third party and we cannot guarantee that your information will remain secure in all situations.

Nanobit may disclose your personal information to third parties as required by law enforcement or other government officials in connection with an investigation of fraud, intellectual property infringements, or other activity that is illegal or may expose you or Nanobit to legal liability. Nanobit may share your information in connection with any merger, sale of our assets, or a financing or acquisition of all or a portion of our business to another company. You will be notified trough notice on our site of any change in ownership or users of your personal information.

All registered Nanobit users may review, update, correct, or delete personal information in their registration profile by changing account settings or contacting us at dpo@nanobit.co. If you completely delete all such information your account may become deactivated. If applicable, all registered Nanobit users may request restriction of processing their personal data and receiving it in a structured, commonly used and machine-readable format. You have the right to lodge a complaint with your national data protection supervisory authority regarding the processing of your personal information.

We will retain your information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide you services. If you wish to cancel your account or request that we no longer use your information to provide you services, please contact us at dpo@nanobit.co and we will attempt to accommodate your request. We will retain and use your information as necessary to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements.

We do not knowingly collect or solicit personal information from anyone under the age of 13 or knowingly allow such persons to use our Service. If you are under 13, please do not send any information about yourself to us, including your name, address, telephone number, or email address. No one under the age of 13 may provide any personal information. In the event that we learn that we have collected personal information from a child under age 13, we will delete that information as soon as possible. If you believe that we might have any information from or about a child under the age of 13, please contact us at dpo@nanobit.co.

We may transfer information that we collect about you to affiliated entities, or to other third parties across borders and from your country or jurisdiction to other countries or jurisdictions around the world where the privacy laws may not be as protective as those in your jurisdiction. Your consent to this Policy followed by your submission of such information represents your agreement to that transfer.

We may update this Policy to reflect changes to our information practices. If we make any material changes, we will notify you by means of a notice on this site prior to the change becoming effective. We encourage you to periodically review this page for the latest information on our privacy practices.
dpo@nanobit.co Nanobit Ltd. Slovenska 23 10 000 Zagreb Croatia If you have any questions about this policy, please contact us at dpo@nanobit.co.

array.string: You get unlimited tickets for unlimited reading for the duration of your subscription.

dict.string: What do I get for joining the My Story Book Club?

array.string: The subscriptions are $2.99 weekly and $7.99 monthly*.
* Prices shown in $USD. Prices may vary by region in accordance with the App Store Pricing Matrix
Subscription means your account will be charged for renewal within 24-hours prior to the end of the current period at the cost of the chosen package.
Your subscription will renew automatically unless auto-renew is turned off for at least 24-hours before the end of the current period.
Subscriptions may be managed by the user and auto-renewal may be turned off by going to the user’s Account Settings after purchase.

dict.string: How can I manage my subscriptions?

array.string: Purchased subscriptions continue for the duration of the subscription period.
No cancellation of the current subscription is allowed during active subscription period.
Any unused portion of a free trial period, if offered, will be forfeited when the user purchases a subscription.
